%o A088028 (define primes '(2 3 5 7 ... 999983)) (compute n) returns A088028(n) (or #f if prime list is too short) computation takes a reasonable amount of time for n <= 16 (slower than "brutal" method for small values of n, but soon becomes much quicker). Result is certified to be the smallest.
